# Reap idle per-cell test workdirs created by the CI workflows. Each
# cell bind-mounts a unique subdir under /scratch (host path embeds
# github.run_id + strategy.job-index; see .github/workflows/test.yml).
# Cleanup mechanics: `e` cleans files older than the Age field, then
# recursively removes empty subdirs that are also old enough -- so a
# completed/crashed cell's tree gets eaten once its contents are >1d
# stale. The scratch dir itself is the rule target and stays. Age=1d
# is comfortably beyond the harness's 1500s timeout, so a live cell
# can't be reaped mid-run.
#
# Production runner workdirs (workdir_<inst>) hold per-job artifacts
# split across:
#  - _work/    : actions/checkout's clone cache; reuse across jobs is a
#                real speedup, so we don't reap.
#  - _temp/    : per-job scratch (downloads, decompressed actions).
#                actions/runner stages each job's tool installs and
#                checkouts under here; safe to reap after a week.
#  - _actions/ : downloaded action repos shared across jobs. Reusable
#                but heavy; 30d covers any reasonable cache window.
# Globbed paths match every workdir_<inst> automatically; rules are
# no-ops on hosts that haven't created any workdirs yet.
#
# Type Path                                              Mode UID GID Age  Argument
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/scratch                -    -   -   1d
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/workdir_*/_temp        -    -   -   7d
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/workdir_*/_actions     -    -   -   30d
